我们不会说，哦，你更重要或者你不重要。

166
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:45,880
Whoever comes first gets it.
谁先来谁就得到它。

167
00:07:45,880 --> 00:07:46,880
All right.
好的。

168
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:49,840
So if I come to the restaurant at five o'clock, I get to sit first.
所以如果我五点来到餐厅，我就先坐下。

169
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:51,680
But if you come at 510, you're next.
但如果你五点十分来，你就排在我后面。

170
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,360
And after you, 530.
你之后，是五点半的人。

171
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:55,080
So it's first come first serve.
所以这就是先到先得。

172
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:57,480
It depends on when you arrive.
这取决于你到达的时间。

173
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,480
That's right.
没错。

174
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:00,560
So obviously this wasn't convenient for us.
所以显然这对我们来说不方便。

175
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:03,400
So we are going to wait until tomorrow.
所以我们打算等到明天。

176
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:06,320
But the airline will put us up in a hotel.
但航空公司会安排我们住酒店。

177
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:08,160
We will put you up in a hotel.
我们会安排你住酒店。

178
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:09,160
All right.
好的。

179
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:12,320
So let's take this as a phrase because we all know what a hotel is.
所以我们把这个当作一个短语，因为大家都知道酒店是什么。

180
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:15,420
It's a place where you stay when you're on holiday or business.
酒店是你度假或出差时住的地方。

181
00:08:15,420 --> 00:08:19,400
But to put someone up, what exactly does this mean?
但“put someone up”到底是什么意思呢？

182
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:23,480
Basically you are paying for that person to stay at that hotel.
基本上就是你为那个人支付住酒店的费用。

183
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:26,760
And you made the reservation and you're going to pay for the room.
而且你做了预订，并会支付房间费用。

184
00:08:26,760 --> 00:08:31,360
So I will put you up means I will pay for your room at a hotel.
所以“I will put you up”意思是我会支付你在酒店的房间费用。

185
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:32,360
Right.
对。

186
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:34,760
And it's usually only for accommodation for a hotel.
而且通常只指酒店住宿。

187
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:37,800
You can't say I will put you up for a meal.
你不能说“I will put you up for a meal”。

188
00:08:37,800 --> 00:08:38,800
No.
不行。

189
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:42,660
But you can say I'll put you up at my house, which means I will let you stay the night
但你可以说“I'll put you up at my house”，意思是我让你在我家过夜，

190
00:08:42,660 --> 00:08:43,660
at my house.
在我家。

191
00:08:43,660 --> 00:08:45,560
So not food, but actually sleeping.
所以不是食物，而是睡觉。

192
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:46,560
Right.
对。

193
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,640
So it usually involves sleeping.
所以通常涉及睡觉。

194
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:49,640
That's right.
没错。

195
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:55,440
So for example, you could say he's coming to our hometown for the wedding.
比如，你可以说他要来我们家乡参加婚礼。

196
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:57,640
I will put him up at my house.
我会安排他住在我家。

197
00:08:57,640 --> 00:08:58,640
Right.
对。

198
00:08:58,640 --> 00:09:03,880
Or if your company sent you to Japan, you say my company put me up at the Hyatt Hotel.
或者如果你的公司派你去日本，你可以说我的公司安排我住在凯悦酒店。

199
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:04,880
Oh, fancy.
哦，真高级。

200
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:05,880
Nice.
不错。

201
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:06,880
All right.
好的。

202
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:08,320
So that's all the phrases we have for you.
这就是我们为你准备的所有短语。

203
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:15,920
Let's listen to our dialogue one last time.
让我们最后听一遍对话。

204
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:17,000
Good afternoon, sir.
下午好，先生。

205
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,240
May I please see your passport and reservation?
请出示您的护照和预订信息好吗？

206
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:20,880
Here you go.
给你。

207
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:23,360
Oh, I'm sorry, sir.
哦，对不起，先生。

208
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:26,480
This flight has been canceled due to some mechanical problems.
这趟航班因机械故障被取消了。

209
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:27,480
Canceled?
取消了？

210
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:29,320
What am I supposed to do now?
我现在该怎么办？

211
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:33,720
We apologize for any inconveniences that may be caused by this.
我们为由此可能造成的不便表示歉意。

212
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:37,600
If your flight is urgent, I could put you on a waiting list for another flight this
如果您的航班很紧急，我可以把您列入今晚另一趟航班的候补名单，

213
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:38,760
evening.
今晚的。

214
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:41,220
But it's on a first come, first serve basis.
但这是按先到先得的原则。

215
00:09:41,220 --> 00:09:44,840
So there's no guarantee you'll be able to take that flight.
所以不能保证您能坐上那趟航班。

216
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:46,320
What are my other options?
我还有其他选择吗？

217
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:51,320
Well, if you can wait until tomorrow, we will put you up in a hotel for today.
嗯，如果您能等到明天，我们今天会安排您住酒店。

218
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:54,200
And you can take the scheduled flight for tomorrow morning.
您可以乘坐明天早上的定期航班。

219
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,200
That's fine.
好的。

220
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,200
I'll do that then.
那我就这么办吧。

221
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,400
Thank you for your understanding, sir.
感谢您的理解，先生。

222
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:59,160
I'll book your flight now.
我现在就为您预订航班。

223
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:00,840
All right.
好的。

224
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:02,560
We're back.
我们回来了。

225
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:06,240
So talking about canceled flights, usually it's due to bad weather.
说到航班取消，通常是因为天气不好。

226
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:09,000
And usually you can catch another flight soon.
而且通常你很快就能赶上另一趟航班。

227
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,520
But sometimes you do have these problems.
但有时确实会遇到这些问题。

228
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:14,600
Like when there was the whole 9-11 thing, I think a lot of flights were canceled or
比如在9·11事件期间，我想很多航班都被取消了，或者

229
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:19,520
the volcano that erupted and European flights were grounded for a long time.
火山爆发导致欧洲航班长时间停飞。

230
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:20,560
Yes, that's right.
是的，没错。

231
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:23,440
So sometimes there are natural disasters.
所以有时是自然灾害。

232
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:25,200
Sometimes there are man-made disasters.
有时是人祸。

233
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:29,600
But you actually said a very interesting word there and something that I think people who
但你刚才说了一个很有趣的词，我觉得学习这个的人

234
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:32,320
are learning about this should definitely study.
应该好好研究一下。

235
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,320
The word is grounded.
这个词是“grounded”。

236
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:35,120
A flight has been grounded.
航班被停飞了。

237
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:36,120
Yes.
是的。

238
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:38,600
That means that the airplane will stay on the ground.
意思是飞机将停在地面上。

239
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,280
It means the plane will not fly.
意思是飞机不会起飞。

240
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:41,280
OK.
好的。

241
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:45,600
So when planes are grounded because of bad weather or because of a natural disaster like
所以当飞机因恶劣天气或自然灾害（比如火山爆发）而停飞时，

242
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:52,960
a volcano, it's a very serious situation because the people who are going to fly can't now.
情况会非常严重，因为原本要坐飞机的人现在走不了了。

243
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:57,600
Now in our dialogue, we saw that they handled it, the airline handled it very, very well.
在我们的对话中，我们看到他们处理得很好，航空公司处理得非常非常好。

244
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:00,240
But I think this is a very rare case.
但我觉得这是非常罕见的情况。

245
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,520
You've had flights canceled before.
你之前遇到过航班取消。

246
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:02,520
How did they handle it?
他们是怎么处理的？

247
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:03,520
I have.
我遇到过。

248
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:06,840
I've had two or three flights canceled one time because of a blizzard.
我有过两三次航班取消，有一次是因为暴风雪。

249
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:08,160
So all flights were grounded.
所以所有航班都停飞了。

250
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:10,760
The weather was very bad, very dangerous.
天气非常糟糕，非常危险。

251
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:13,040
And the airline company said, well, we're sorry.
然后航空公司说，嗯，我们很抱歉。

252
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:14,680
There are no more flights.
没有更多航班了。

253
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:17,240
But if you come back tomorrow, we can help you.
但如果你明天再来，我们可以帮你。

254
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:20,680
And I was very lucky because they did not give me a hotel.
我很幸运，因为他们没有给我安排酒店。

255
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:22,560
They did not put me up in a hotel.
他们没有给我安排住宿。

256
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:24,000
But I was staying with a friend.
但我当时住在朋友那里。

257
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:27,040
So my friends put me up at her house.
所以我朋友让我住在她家。

258
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:32,840
But the other time the flight was canceled, the airline put me on a flight from another
但另一次航班取消时，航空公司把我安排到了另一家

259
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:34,520
company, another airline company.
航空公司的航班上。

260
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:39,600
And so sometimes they can do that where they have a relationship with another airline company,
所以有时候他们可以这样做，如果和另一家航空公司有关系的话，

261
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:40,600
they can do that.
他们就能做到。

262
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:43,240
So usually they do try to handle it relatively well.
所以通常他们确实会尽量处理得相对好一些。

263
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:49,080
But I've heard sometimes that they are not very understanding or very sympathetic to
但我听说有时候他们对自己造成的

264
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:50,640
the inconvenience they cause.
不便并不太理解或同情。

265
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:51,640
Definitely.
确实。

266
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:55,480
And I think the worst is when it's bad weather because everyone's angry.
我觉得最糟糕的是天气不好的时候，因为每个人都很生气。

267
00:11:55,480 --> 00:11:59,840
And all the customers need to go somewhere, but they can't because there are no flights.
所有乘客都需要去某个地方，但他们去不了，因为没有航班。

268
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:04,160
And so the people who are working for the airlines get very frustrated or upset.
所以航空公司的工作人员会变得非常沮丧或烦躁。

269
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:05,160
Right.
没错。

270
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:06,800
Because basically it's not their fault.
因为基本上这不是他们的错。

271
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:07,800
It's not their fault.
不是他们的错。

272
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:08,800
There's bad weather.
是天气不好。

273
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:11,560
So there's not really much compensation the company can give you.
所以公司能给你的补偿其实不多。

274
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:12,680
No, definitely not.
不，确实不多。

275
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:13,680
Not really their fault.
真不是他们的错。

276
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:18,320
But it's hard not to get frustrated because you want to go home, you're tired, you don't
但很难不感到沮丧，因为你想回家，你很累，你不想

277
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:20,400
want to pay for another night in a hotel.
再付一晚酒店的钱。

278
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:22,800
So I can understand both sides.
所以我能理解双方。

279
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:23,800
Right.
没错。

280
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:28,720
Well, it's an interesting topic and I'm sure many of our listeners who have traveled have
嗯，这是个有趣的话题，我相信很多旅行过的听众都

281
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:30,720
had a flight delayed or canceled.
遇到过航班延误或取消。

282
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:33,800
So you can come to our website and share your story with us.
所以你可以来我们的网站分享你的故事。

283
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:36,200
And of course, if you have any questions or comments.
当然，如果你有任何问题或评论。

284
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:38,280
You can find us at EnglishPod.com.
你可以在EnglishPod.com找到我们。

285
00:12:38,280 --> 00:12:39,280
We hope to see you all there.
我们希望能在那里见到大家。

286
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:40,280
All right.
好了。

287
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:41,280
Bye.
再见。

288
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:43,280
Bye.
再见。
